The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, April 24, 2004 				 Drug cloud on babu
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, April 23: The CBI suspects the brother of tainted bureaucrat Sandeep Garg could be involved in a drug racket.																								The CBI, while investigating the disproportionate assets of Garg, a 1991-batch IAS officer of the Haryana cadre who was arrested last week after accepting a bribe, came across documents relating to a pharmaceutical firm in Ghaziabad.																								On paper, a bureau official said, the company was owned by Gargs brother, Sanjeev. The CBI suspects the firm could be manufacturing spurious drugs. 																								Sleuths recovered samples of drugs during raids on Sanjeevs office, factory and residence last evening. 
